President Biden spoke at the Ted M. Gallegos Community Center in Albuquerque, New Mexico. He expressed his commitment to defeating cancer and mentioned the loss of his son to the disease. He also highlighted the importance of unity and confidence in America's capabilities. President Biden discussed his administration's efforts to rebuild the economy, invest in infrastructure, lower drug prices, and address student debt. He criticized the Republican Party's plans to cut Social Security and Medicare, restrict abortion rights, and suppress voting. President Biden urged the audience to vote and expressed his optimism for America's future.